<html><head><meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"><meta charset="utf-8"></head><body><pre>{"id":1845,"date":"2025-09-26T16:34:03","date_gmt":"2025-09-26T06:34:03","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/?page_id=1845"},"modified":"2025-09-27T12:05:24","modified_gmt":"2025-09-27T02:05:24","slug":"unions-past-present","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/unions-past-present\/","title":{"rendered":"Unions: Past &amp;amp; Present"},"content":{"rendered":"\n&lt;p&gt;We\u2019re starting up a new discussion group called &lt;strong&gt;Unions: Past &amp;amp; Present&lt;\/strong&gt;!&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;We\u2019ll be looking at range of historical union struggles in Australia from the Clarrie O\u2019Shea general strike in 1969, to the BLF\u2019s green bans and the 1998 Waterfront dispute. We\u2019ll talk about the lessons we can learn from these disputes and how they apply to contemporary examples of organising like the 2021 Geelong Library strikes. We\u2019ll also discuss broader union theory and strategy and the organising context we find ourselves in today.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We will assume a little bit of background knowledge, so it\u2019s open to anyone who has already completed our introductory education sequence &amp;#8211; the Anarchist Political School.&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;All sessions will consist of a reading, which we read and discuss together, as well as some &lt;strong&gt;optional&lt;\/strong&gt; additional reading to provide more context if you&amp;#8217;re particularly interested. Unions: Past &amp;amp; Present is completely free. All sessions are run in a wheelchair accessible location nearby to public transport. Each discussion goes for 90 minutes.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;To participate and for more information,&lt;strong&gt; fill in the expression of interest form below&lt;\/strong&gt;, or send us an email at &lt;em&gt;melbourne@ancomfed.org&lt;\/em&gt;!&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-black-color\"&gt;Upcoming Sessions:&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt; Carlton&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/h2&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;ul class=\"wp-block-list\"&gt;\n&lt;li&gt;ACF-M Union Strategy,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;Monday&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt; 6 October, 6:30pm&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/mark&gt;&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/li&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;li&gt;The Builders&amp;#8217; Labourers Federation (BLF),&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;mark style=\"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)\" class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\"&gt;Monday&lt;\/mark&gt;&l